```json
{
  "application": "PBS",
  "details": {
    "resources": {
      "processors": 1,
      "memory": "4GB",
      "walltime": "100 hours",
      "queue": "fluxod",
      "qos": "flux"
    },
    "modules": [
      "R/3.5.0",
      "r-biomed-libs/3.5.0"
    ],
    "software": [
      "Rscript"
    ],
    "commands": [
      "cat $PBS_NODEFILE",
      "qstat -f $PBS_JOBID",
      "cd $PBS_O_WORKDIR",
      "make data/temp/best_hp_results_Decision_Tree_$seed.csv",
      "Rscript code/learning/main.R $seed \"Decision_Tree\"",
      "echo \"Script complete\"",
      "echo \"qsub working directory absolute is\"",
      "echo $PBS_O_WORKDIR",
      "qstat -f $PBS_JOBID",
      "exit"
    ],
    "script_type": "shell"
  }
}
```

This script is using **PBS** (Portable Batch System) to manage the execution of the job. It's defining various resources needed by the script, including processors, memory, walltime, and queue. It then loads modules for R and R biomed libraries. The script utilizes the array functionality of PBS to run multiple instances of the job with different parameters. It uses Rscript to execute an R script for machine learning, likely related to decision tree algorithms.
